Explained: Why Trump is aiming for ‘400 paar’ after Biden’s withdrawal

Jul 22, 2024, 13:31 (IST)

Biden's exit from the US presidential race has thrown the Democrat campaign in disarray. How things went so wrong for him, what his vice-president Kamala Harris now needs to do to secure her party's nomination, and why the Trump campaign is dreaming of a landslide 400 electoral votes

INS Brahmaputra suffers damage after major fire, one sailor missing

timesofindia.com / Jul 22, 2024, 23:04 (IST)

A fire broke out on the Indian Naval Ship Brahmaputra on Monday evening, causing the vessel to lean heavily to its port side. The Indian Navy stated that one junior sailor is currently missing, and a search operation is ongoing to locate the individual.The incident took place while the INS Brahmaputra, described as a "multi-role Frigate," was undergoing refit at ND (Mbi), according to a statement released by the Indian Navy.

'You may clap': Kamala Harris' 'awkward' 1st speech on Biden's retirement. Watch

timesofindia.com / Jul 22, 2024, 23:11 (IST)

This was Vice President Kamala Harris' first speech Monday after President Joe Biden endorsed her as the Democratic presidential nominee for the election as Biden announced to withdraw from the race. Obviously, all eyes were on Kamala as she is speculated to challenge Donald Trump in the November election. And as soon as it ended, the verdict was out. It was awkward with Kamala Harris' trademark 'laugh'.

Why scientists want to dig a 6-km deep hole in Maharashtra’s Koyna

timesofindia.com / Jul 22, 2024, 15:34 (IST)

The Koyna region has experienced thousands of big and small earthquakes ever since a dam was built there in 1962. Is the weight of the water in the reservoir making the ground creak? A deep hole might reveal what’s going on underground
